{
  "texts": [
    "Our classification of error types remains consistent with that of Du et al., ensuring easier comparison [17].",
    "'Boundary mismatch' denotes discrepancies in the span range of entities between machine-annotated and humanannotated results.",
    "'False positive' refers to entities identified by the proposed model that aren't present in the gold standard, while 'false negative' indicates entities the model failed to extract.",
    "'Incorrect entity type' pertains to instances where, though the entity's span range is accurate, the entity itself has been misclassified.",
    "It is evident that the model exhibits a predominant challenge in dealing with boundary mismatch, false positives and false negatives, which can be attributed to several factors."
  ]
}